      "id": "PR_kwDOQElFyc6up0h9",
      "title": "Specify computation",
      "url": "https://github.com/cjpatton/draft-hoypat-httpbis-message-signatures-ekm/pull/1",
      "state": "MERGED",
      "author": "jhoyla",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "The output of the EKM needs to be in ASCII, so we should base64 encode it.\r\nI don't think we'll need a context string, although maybe we should add one for the version of TLS we're using, i.e. TLS 1.3, QUIC, some future version, etc.? It affects the output of the computation, and so, in theory, we could be vulnerable to a channel synchronisation attack where a TLS 1.3 session and a QUIC session happen to derive the same `exporter_master_secret` but to be honest if the attacker can achieve that then we have bigger problems to worry about. ",
      "createdAt": "2025-10-20T15:15:53Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-10-20T16:50:59Z",
