              "originalPosition": 7,
              "body": "I'm not too worried about confusing with QUIC. In our threat model, the server is honest and is therefore always injecting entropy that makes the EKM unique.\n\nIt might be a good idea to at least identify the TLS version in the context string. First this emphasizes that we aren't planning on backwards compatibility, and it also avoids confusing with future versions.",
